0permission%20to%20train%20ChatGPT.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20case%20is%20now%20in%20the%20discovery%20phase%2C%20where%20both%20sides%20gather%20and%20exchange%20evidence%20before%20the%20trial.%20As%20part%20of%20that%2C%20OpenAI%20requested%20to%20know%20more%20about%20how%20the%20Times%20uses%20generative%20AI%2C%20including%20its%20use%20of%20generative%20AI%20tools%20from%20other%20companies%2C%20any%20AI%20tools%20it's%20developing%20for%20its%20reporting%2C%20and%20its%20views%20on%20the%20technology.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJudge%20Ona%20T.%20Wang%20rejected%20that%20request%20on%20Friday%2C%20calling%20it%20irrelevant.%20She%20then%20offered%20an%20analogy%20to%20explain%20her%20decision%2C%20comparing%20OpenAI%20to%20a%20video%20game%20manufacturer%20and%20the%20Times%20to%20a%20copyright%20holder.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Csection%3EIf%20a%20copyright%20holder%20sued%20a%20video%20game%20manufacturer%20for%20copyright%20infringement%2C%20the%20copyright%20holder%20might%20be%20required%20to%20produce%20documents%20relating%20to%20their%20interactions%20with%20that%20video%20game%20manufacturer%2C%20but%20the%20video%20game%20manufacturer%20would%20not%20be%20entitled%20to%20wide-ranging%20discovery%20concerning%20the%20copyright%20holder's%20employees'%20gaming%20history%2C%20statements%20about%20video%20games%20generally%2C%20or%20even%20their%20licensing%20of%20different%20content%20to%20other%20video%20game%20Manufacturers.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20same%20case%2C%20legal%20filings%20revealed%20earlier%20this%20month%20that%20OpenAI%20engineers%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-delete-legal-data-lawsuit-new-york-times-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccidentally%20deleted%20evidence%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20Times%20lawyers%20had%20gathered%20from%20their%20servers.%20Lawyers%20for%20the%20outlet%20spent%20over%20150%20hours%20searching%20through%20OpenAI's%20training%20data%20for%20instances%20of%20infringement%2C%20which%20they%20stored%20on%20virtual%20machines%20the%20company%20created.%20The%20majority%20of%20the%20data%20has%20been%20recovered%2C%20and%20the%20Times%20lawyer%20said%20there%20is%20no%20reason%20to%20believe%20it%20was%20%26quot%3Bintentional.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20case%20is%20one%20among%20dozens%20of%20copyright%20cases%20filed%20against%20OpenAI%2C%20including%20by%20media%20organizations%20like%20the%20New%20York%20Daily%20News%2C%20the%20Denver%20Post%2C%20and%20The%20Intercept.%20Some%20of%20these%20cases%20have%20already%20been%20dismissed.%20Earlier%20this%20month%20a%20federal%20judge%20dismissed%20cases%20from%20Raw%20Story%20and%20AlterNet%2C%20because%20the%20outlets%20did%20not%20demonstrate%20%26quot%3Bconcrete%26quot%3B%20harm%20from%20OpenAI's%20actions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOpenAI%20is%20also%20facing%20lawsuits%20from%20authors%2C%20including%20one%20involving%20comedian%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-sarah-silverman-lawsuit-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESarah%20Silverman%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Silverman%20and%20over%20a%20dozen%20authors%20filed%20an%20initial%20complaint%20against%20OpenAI%20in%202023%2C%20saying%20the%20tech%20company%20illegally%20used%20their%20books%20to%20train%20ChatGPT.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMuch%20of%20the%20material%20in%20OpenAI's%20training%20datasets%2C%20however%2C%20comes%20from%20copyrighted%20works%20%E2%80%94%20including%20books%20written%20by%20Plaintiffs%20%E2%80%94%20that%20were%20copied%20by%20OpenAI%20without%20consent%2C%20without%20credit%2C%20and%20without%20compensation%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20complaint%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOpenAI's%20website%20says%20the%20company%20develops%20ChatGPT%20and%20its%20other%20services%20using%20three%20sources%3A%20publicly%20available%20information%20online%2C%20information%20accessed%20by%20partnering%20with%20third%20parties%2C%20and%20information%20provided%20or%20generated%20by%20its%