2C%20which%20could%20present%20problems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20are%20the%20rules%3F%26quot%3B%20he%20asked.%20%26quot%3BIs%20it%20OK%20that%20%E2%80%A6%20it's%20the%20equivalent%20of%20Mark%20Zuckerberg%20as%20just%20the%20surrogate%20parent%20who%20gets%20to%20decide%20what%20your%20kid%20learns%20and%20doesn't%20learn.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESchmidt%20said%20that's%20why%20the%20world%20should%20design%20safety%20requirements%20for%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPlaying%20with%20the%20way%20people%20think%20is%20really%20powerful%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20think%20about%20state-sponsored%20misinformation%2C%20that's%20trivial%20compared%20to%20having%20your%20best%20friend%20be%20state-sponsored%2C%20and%20they%20sort%20of%20have%20daily%20interaction%20and%20shape%20someone's%20identity%2C%20their%20cultural%20values.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20added%3A%20%26quot%3BIn%20the%20case%20where%20AI%20is%20built%20by%20one%20country%2C%20hopefully%20the%20US%2C%20what%20happens%20to%20all%20the%20other%20cultures%3F%20Do%20we%20just%20roll%20through%20them%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20humanity's%20transition%20to%20AI%20will%20be%20rocky%20and%20that%20much%20remains%20to%20be%20seen%20about%20how%20humans%20will%20integrate%20with%20the%20technology.%20One%20audience%20member%20asked%20if%20most%20people%20will%20use%20a%20personal%20AI%20for%20%26quot%3Bvideos%20that%20make%20them%20laugh%26quot%3B%20or%20for%20%26quot%3Binformation%20that's%20only%20going%20to%20confirm%20their%20biases.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOne%20of%20the%20things%20that's%20worth%20saying%20is%20that%20none%20of%20us%20thought%2C%20when%20we%20invented%20social%20media%2C%20that%20we%20would%20become%20a%20threat%20to%20democracy%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20responded.%20%26quot%3BThat%20wasn't%20on%20the%20list%20of%20attributes.%20And%20these%20are%20the%20unintended%20effects%20of%20technologies%20that%20touch%20humans.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp