emiconductor%20company.%20I%20lived%20in%20San%20Francisco%2C%20right%20on%20the%20edge%20of%20Mission%20and%20Portero%20Hill%2C%20and%20commuted%20to%20work%20in%20Santa%20Clara.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2243e8d60c-84c4-440b-9543-698dc31db1f3%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ESilicon%20Valley%20was%20a%20hub%20of%20innovation%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%202010s%20and%20early%202020s%2C%20California%20was%20the%20place%20to%20be%20if%20you%20wanted%20to%20do%20tech%2C%20engineering%2C%20or%20renewable%20energy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20Applied%20Materials%2C%20I%20was%20learning%20how%20to%20be%20an%20engineer%20in%20the%20real%20world.%20But%20I%20wasn't%20working%20on%20energy%20efficiency%20or%20renewable%20energy%2C%20which%20was%20my%20dream.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20found%20that%20I%20was%20clashing%20with%20the%20culture%20of%20Silicon%20Valley.%20There%20are%20a%20ton%20of%20amazing%20people%20there%2C%20but%20generally%20speaking%2C%20I%20felt%20like%20people%20could%20be%20%26quot%3Bfake%20nice.%26quot%3B%20I%20attributed%20that%20attitude%20to%20the%20Silicon%20Valley%20atmosphere.%20I%20don't%20want%20to%20call%20it%20cutthroat%2C%20but%20it%20was%20tough%20at%20times%20to%20join%20a%20community%20of%20really%20driven%20people%20who%20would%20sometimes%20drive%20themselves%20over%20the%20edge.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20more%20of%20a%20%26quot%3Bgo-at-your-own-pace%26quot%3B%20kind%20of%20person.%20I%20don't%20think%2016-hour%20days%20are%20a%20path%20to%20success.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Silicon%20Valley%2C%20you%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20Google%20people%2C%20a%20lot%20of%20Meta%20people%2C%20and%2C%20at%20the%20time%20I%20was%20there%2C%20a%20lot%20of%20Tesla%20people.%20And%20that's%20the%20core%20of%20who%20they%20are.%20I%20grew%20tired%20of%20the%20way%20people%20would%20define%20themselves%20by%20their%20jobs%20rather%20than%20who%20they%20are%20as%20a%20person.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Aerial%20view%20of%20Silicon%20Valley.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F661feeec20b15f0ff428c615%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20aerial%20view%20of%20Silicon%20Valley.%3Cp%3ESmith%20Collection%2FGado%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224083f0fb-0f24-46b6-b350-9cf542d17a6a%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ELeaving%20California%20was%20always%20in%20the%20back%20of%20my%20mind%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20graduating%2C%20I%20was%20worried%20I%20would%20have%20to%20choose%20between%20staying%20in%20California%20and%20having%20a%20career%20I%20liked%20or%20leaving%20California%20and%20having%20a%20career%20I%20didn't%20like.%20The%20career%20opportunities%20in%20Silicon%20Valley%20seemed%20more%20abundant.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20ending%20up%20with%20a%20career%20that%20wasn't%20what%20I%20wanted%20while%20I%20was%20in%20California%20helped%20push%20me%20to%20take%20the%20next%20step.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202022%2C%20I%20started%20applying%20to%20East%20Coast%20jobs%2C%20specifically%20looking%20for%20roles%20in%20renewable%20energy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20got%20an%20offer%20from%20my%20current%20workplace%2C%20Carbon%20Reform%2C%20in%20September%202022.%20They're%20a%20Philadelphia-based%20startup%20working%20on%20sustainability.%20It%20was%20right%20up%20my%20alley.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20moved%20back%20and%20started%20at%20the%20end%20of%20November%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20definitely%20had%20some%20nerves%20before%20moving.%20I%20was%20questioning%20whether%20this%20was%20right%20for%20my%20career.%20The%20sustainability%20hub%20is%20in%20Silicon%20Valley%2C%20and%20moving%20to%20the%20other%20side%20of%20the%20country%20felt%20like%20I%20was%20separating%20myself%20from%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20I%20was%20also%20so%20excited.%20It%20felt%20surreal%20that%20I%20had%20found%20something%20I%20wanted%20to%20do%2C%20and%20I%20got%20the%20bonus%20of%20being%20on%20the%20E