act%20quickly%20to%20market%20developments%2C%20switching%20strategies%20when%20economic%20conditions%20change.%20This%20can%20lead%20to%20greater%20short-term%20gains%20as%20well%20as%20losses.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fpassive-vs-active-investing%23%3A~%3Atext%3DActive%2520investing%2520for%2520market%2520opportunities%2Cyou%2520think%2520conditions%2520will%2520reverse.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPassive%20investing%3C%2Fa%3E%20tends%20to%20yield%20higher%20net%20returns%20in%20the%20long%20run%20in%20comparison%2C%20making%20it%20relatively%20safer%20and%20more%20popular%20amongst%20risk-averse%20traders%2C%20but%20in%20the%20process%2C%20it's%20made%20active%20investing%20riskier%2C%20Sl%C3%B8k%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHigher%20passive%20ownership%20can%20increase%20volatility%2C%20lower%20market%20liquidity%2C%20and%20increase%20market%20concentration%20in%20large%20cap%20names%20such%20as%20the%20so-called%20'Magnificent%20Seven%2C'%26quot%3B%20Sl%C3%B8k%20wrote%20in%20a%20recent%20paper.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20that%20the%20massive%20shift%20toward%20passive%20investing%20has%20resulted%20in%20greater%20price%20spikes%20and%20dips%20as%20investor%20demand%20has%20become%20less%20reactive%20to%20stock%20prices.%20It's%20also%20resulted%20in%20a%20less%20actively%20traded%20market%2C%20where%20mispricing%20can%20be%20greater%20and%20last%20for%20longer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20two%20factors%20drive%20greater%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frecession-fears-fueling-stock-market-crash-wall-street-chaos-positive-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emarket%20volatility%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20has%20been%20on%20the%20rise%20recently.%20The%20Cboe%20volatility%20index%20up%20almost%2030%25%20in%20the%20last%20six%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20more%20active%20investors%20turning%20passive%2C%20there%20are%20also%20fewer%20investors%20shorting%20stocks%2C%20Sl%C3%B8k%20said.%20If%20the%20trend%20continues%2C%20shorts%20will%20be%20%26quot%3Bsqueezed%20out%26quot%3B%20more%20easily%2C%20which%20will%20boost%20volatility%20in%20large-cap%20shares%20and%20put%20upward%20pressure%20on%20their%20prices.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20that%20makes%20it%20riskier%20to%20short%20large-caps%2C%20which%20will%20only%20fuel%20a%20greater%20shift%20to%20passive%20flows.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20short%2C%20when%20active%20investors%20turn%20passive%2C%20large-cap%20stocks%20will%20benefit%20disproportionately.%20This%20dynamic%20can%20be%20observed%20in%20the%20price-to-earnings%20(P%2FE)%20ratios%20of%20large-%20and%20mega-cap%20stocks%2C%20which%20have%20been%20consistently%20high%20and%20growing%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPassive%20investing%20has%20rocketed%20in%20popularity%20in%20the%20past%20three%20decades%2C%20accounting%20for%2050%25%20of%20total%20equity%20investing%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fmutual-funds%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emutual%20funds%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fwhat-is-an-etf%23%3A~%3Atext%3DETFs%2520tend%2520to%2520be%2520highly%2Chow%2520you%2520look%2520at%2520liquidity.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EETFs%3C%2Fa%3E%20globally%2C%20almost%20double%20what%20it%20was%20in%202012%2C%20Sl%C3%B8k%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpassive-investing-stock-market-risk-volatile-investors-apollo-2024-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1732368661000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66acfe3aa5247369a3e91a0c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fetf%2Fpassive-investing-stock-market-risk-volatile-i